lines: to empty a drawer of rhetorical beetles
to dance in a descending tempo
to alight upon a gabled silence
to collapse under a pile of invisible ketchup
to recalibrate your coat with obsolete salt
to dent the margin of reluctant starlings
to haunt the curvature of quiet copper
to snuggle with a sarcastic accordion
to preface a thought with licorice
to be laced with provincial glass
to whisper secrets to a carton
